\chapter{EXEMPLARY Robot Arm Demos}

This tutorial shows how to move a UR5 robot arm from one pose to another
by clicking buttons and dragging targets in a graphical interface using RRT-Connect planner.
Although we use RRT-Connect as an illustrative example, any planner provided by OMPL can be applied to this scenario.

In this tutorial, we present a simple but complete pipeline for robotic arm motion planning.
Using OMPL as the motion planner, PyRoKi for inverse kinematics and collision checking, and Viser as an interactive visualizer, we demonstrate how a robot arm can move from one configuration to another in joint space.

