\section{Main function}

Main loop that continuously updates the environment, checks collisions, and updates the robot configuration
either by playing back a planned path or by solving IK interactively.

\begin{lstlisting}
while True:
    t0 = time.time()
\end{lstlisting}
We save t0 to measure how much time is taken to find a path.

\begin{lstlisting}
obs_dict = get_obstacles()
cc.set_obs(obs_dict)
\end{lstlisting}
We update the obstacles to the collision checker.

\begin{lstlisting}
if is_playing and path is not None:

    if path_i < len(path):
        q_current = path[path_i]
        path_i += 1

    elif path_i == len(path):
        q_current = path[0]
        path_i = 1
\end{lstlisting}
We first check whether path is found with the interactive solve button,
and we get one waypoint from the waypoint list and update it into current configuration.
and then if the path has reached the goal state, we loop back to the start configuration.

\begin{lstlisting}
ik_result = PyrokiHelper.solve_ik_with_collision(
